org.whispercomm.c2dm4j.async.handler
Interface Context<T,E extends Enum<E>>

Type Parameters:
T - the type of object to which to associate context
E - the enumeration of possible decisions
public interface Context<T,E extends Enum<E>>

Context associated with an object (i.e., Message, Response, or Throwable) in the asynchronous flow. The context holds

  • the object,
  • the Future returned by the AsyncC2dmManager.pushMessage(Message) method call,
  • the delay before the object should be sent or retried,
  • the decision (delay, retry, return, etc.) for the object, and
  • an object map for MessageFilter, and ResponseHandler, and ThrowableHandler instances to store message-specific context.

Author:
David R. Bild

put

void put(Object key,
         Object value)
Adds an key-value pair to the internal context map. Handlers and filters should use the following convention. Each handler (filter) may store one value, using the handler's canonical name (.getClass().getCanonicalName()) as the key. If multiple instances of the same type are allowable, the key should be composed of the canonical name and a instance identifier. Handlers needing multiple values should store a map.

Parameters:
key - the key for the context map--- the handler class's canonical name, by convention
value - the value to store--- often a Map
